# fedora-bootstrap — scoped passwordless-sudo allowlist for the ClaudeBox operating user.
#
# Installed to /etc/sudoers.d/claudebox by setup-host.sh, validated with `visudo` first.
# The user is a normal `wheel` admin (sudo WITH a password). This file grants passwordless
# sudo for ONLY the EXACT commands below, so the non-interactive in-box Claude Code can run
# those — and NOTHING else — without a password. Every other `sudo` still requires the
# password, so the agent is OS-blocked from it.
#
# SECURITY — NO WILDCARDS on file-capable commands. `tailscale serve`/`funnel` accept a
# local FILE or DIRECTORY path as their target; run as root they READ and EXPOSE it — over
# the tailnet (serve) or the PUBLIC INTERNET (funnel): /etc/shadow, TLS/SSH host keys, the
# tailscale node keys, anything root can read. So a bare `serve *` is a full root-secret
# disclosure. Every serve entry below is therefore PINNED to an EXACT http://127.0.0.1:PORT
# loopback target, never a wildcard, and `funnel` is intentionally ABSENT.
#
# GROW THIS LIST ONLY HERE, by review: ClaudeBox proposes a NEW EXACT line (e.g. another
# pinned loopback port it must expose), you commit it, and re-running setup re-stamps it
# (policy/CLAUDE.md: "propose; the user commits"). Every entry must be a FULL command with
# its EXACT arguments and NO trailing wildcard. NEVER add: a wildcard on serve/funnel, a
# file/dir/text: target, `funnel`, a node-changing subcommand (up/down/set/login/logout),
# or any command that can spawn a shell or run arbitrary programs.
#
# __USER__ is replaced with the operating user (default: core) at install time by setup-host.sh.
#
# HOST SELF-APPLY (#133) — the ONE deliberate exception to "the host-apply gate stays with the operator".
# /usr/local/sbin/host-apply is a ROOT-OWNED, argument-free, no-wildcard executor: it applies ONLY
# merge-gated `main` (fetched from a PINNED canonical URL, run from a pristine `git archive` of the exact
# fetched sha — never the core-writable clone's working tree), fast-forward-only, health-gated with
# rollback + a fail-closed readback. So the agent can trigger the apply but can INJECT NOTHING it runs —
# this grants "apply the already-approved code", NOT arbitrary root (the merge gate is the real boundary;
# recovery is automatic, not a click). It is exactly ONE fixed command with NO argument and NO wildcard,
# honouring the no-wildcard/no-shell-spawn discipline above (host-apply owns its own inputs; the sudoers
# surface exposes none). Grown by review here, like every entry. Full trust chain: host-apply.sh header.

Cmnd_Alias CLAUDEBOX_HOST = /usr/bin/tailscale serve --bg --https=443 http\://127.0.0.1\:9090, \
                            /usr/bin/tailscale serve status, \
                            /usr/bin/tailscale serve status --json, \
                            /usr/bin/tailscale status, \
                            /usr/bin/tailscale status --json

Cmnd_Alias CLAUDEBOX_APPLY = /usr/local/sbin/host-apply

__USER__ ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: CLAUDEBOX_HOST, CLAUDEBOX_APPLY
